Good work always starts with having a good workspace. Clean up an area to work on. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/18\/Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-1Bullet1-Version-2.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-1Bullet1-Version-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/18\/Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-1Bullet1-Version-2.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-1Bullet1-Version-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Pick up any objects that you wouldn't like to be damaged. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/2\/2e\/Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-1Bullet2-Version-2.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-1Bullet2-Version-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/2\/2e\/Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-1Bullet2-Version-2.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-1Bullet2-Version-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Clamp the torch head and gas canister to the table (follow instructions provided by the manufacturer).

You will get a thin string of glass, just allow the flame to melt through it. Place your glass rod onto the rod rest, out of the way. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/54/Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-14Bullet1-Version-3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-14Bullet1-Version-3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/54/Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-14Bullet1-Version-3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-14Bullet1-Version-3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

You may want to switch your mandrel into your dominant hand at this point. To do this, carefully bring the mandrel in front of the torch. Never try reach over the flame. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5c/Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-14Bullet2-Version-3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-14Bullet2-Version-3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5c/Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-14Bullet2-Version-3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Your-Own-Glass-Beads-from-Scratch-Step-14Bullet2-Version-3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
